[USER] I'm trying to swap OSMO for ATOM but the transaction keeps failing
[AGENT] Hi there! I'd be happy to help you with your swap issue. Can you tell me what error message you're seeing?
[USER] It says 'insufficient funds' but I have enough OSMO in my wallet
[AGENT] That usually indicates you don't have enough OSMO to cover the gas fees. Do you have at least 0.1 OSMO extra for transaction fees?
[USER] Oh I see, let me add more OSMO for gas
[AGENT] Perfect! Make sure to keep some OSMO for gas fees in future transactions. Let me know if you need any other help!

[USER] How do I provide liquidity to a pool?
[AGENT] Hi! I'd be glad to help you with liquidity provision. Are you looking to add liquidity to an existing pool or create a new one?
[USER] I want to add to the OSMO/USDC pool
[AGENT] Great choice! Go to the Pools tab, find the OSMO/USDC pool, click 'Add Liquidity', enter your amounts, and confirm the transaction
[USER] Do I need equal amounts of both tokens?
[AGENT] Yes, you'll need equivalent dollar values of both OSMO and USDC. The interface will automatically calculate the ratio for you
